        <bioghist id="ref5">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Bernard Mannes Baruch was a financier and head of several war committees, including chairman of the War Industries Board, 1918-1919, and U.S. representative to the United Nations Atomic Energy Commission, 1946.</p>
